name: Pura Tirta Empul
address: Tampaksiring, Gianyar Regency, Bali 80552, Indonesia
review 1:
First, we didn't do the ritual cleansing as so many people queuing, and we arrived late afternoon. Guide explained to us we cleaned from water flowing from left to right. Queue after queue until the end.
I wish we had arrived earlier so we had time.
We walked around the temples. Some areas won't let you take towels (even dry) in, or if you're wet, you couldn't enter.
Nice special temples. Locals also come here to pray and cleanse.
The stalls on the exit way were a bit annoying. I was checking on a painting. The shop owner initially said 300k. Then I said I was just checking, and she put down to 200k. I really had no intention to buy and walked she had it to 100k.
I am not used to negotiating, so I would rather shop at a place that has price tags.
Also, ATM at temple charges 30k for every withdrawal and limits 1000k each withdrawal.
Bring cash with you here.
review 2: a super cool temple in the middle of the jungle. the special thing about this temple is that you can cleanse yourself, whether you are a local or a traveler. I was most interested in the villa of the President of Indonesia....ðŸ¤©ðŸ’ªðŸ’ªI will definitely come again
review 3: Amazing experience! As you enter youâ€™re going to need a sarong which is included in your entry ticket. If youâ€™re interested in going into the water youâ€™re going to need a bathing sarong, this one you pay for. It wasnâ€™t very busy so the visit was smooth. Itâ€™s a great way to experience the culture and traditions. I definitely recommend visiting.
review 4: Amazing experience, and the tour guide is so helpful with the history explanation, you can go bathing for peace of mind but the queue is contradictive with that, but it did teach you patient lol! Great tourist place, so many art stalls and shops, also the water springs are eyes-opening! Also need to buy tickets to entry.
review 5: Totally worth the trip, cleansing with holy water and beautiful ancient architecture. It has nature springs and fish pools, thousands of years old trees too. Better bring a sarong of your own for bathing. Entrance fee cash only. Bring dry clothes for change after if you want to go in the pool.

name: Pura Mengening
address: Jalan Tirta No.25M, Sareseda, Tampaksiring, Kec. Tampaksiring, Kabupaten Gianyar, Bali 80552, Indonesia
review 1: A green water oasis with 12 different holy waters. There's the option to do the "purification" procedure.. It takes like 15min. They provide orange rental sarong but it's recommended to bring swim wear. Much less crowded than the close by "Julia Roberts" temple
review 2:
Very nice ritual, we paid 30k for entry and 35k for offerings.
They gave us sarongs at the entry and one guy explained to us the usage of the springs and every step we had to do for purification
Nice location, very few tourists, you pay 10k for a locker and there are some exchange rooms, donâ€™t expect luxury
review 3:
Beautiful, less busy, and even nicer than Tirta Empul if you must choose between them.  The water prayer is very immersive and peaceful and takes maybe 20+ minutes when not busy.

About 30000 cash to enter per person.
review 4:
This was quite the experience! Such a wonderful blessing. Be forewarned that women on their cycles aren't allowed in the water. They gave us a dry sarong to wear down there, another to wear that got wet and then the dry one when you're done. Everyone wears a sarong. There isn't a particular swimsuit rule- I saw one pieces and 2 pieces, but you must wear the sarong. The bathroom is less than desirable, so try to go beforehand. There are a lot of old ladies trying to sell bracelets and necklaces in the parking lot and they can be aggressive, just FYI.

Overall it was a neat experience and the chilly water felt good on a hot day. They do have lockers with a key for 10,000 IDR or you could use it without a lock.
review 5:
Beautiful 11th century temple used for water purification ceremonies. Far less crowded than other larger  temples on the tourist radar but in my opinion even more beautiful.
It was an honour and privilege to have spent time with and experienced a water purification ceremony performed by Putu Suciyati, her mum and cousin. They truly are beautiful, genuine humans, so in touch with there spiritually. The ceremony took around 3hrs and if you get the chance, I guarantee it will be a highlight of your Bali trip.

name: Istana Kepresidenan Tampaksiring
address: Jl. Dr. Ir. Soekarno, Manukaya, Kec. Tampaksiring, Kabupaten Gianyar, Bali 80552, Indonesia
review 1: Out of the six palaces, Tampaksiring was built after Indonesian independence. Balinese style merges with modernism is the primary elaboration for the architecture of the palace. Even more, next to the palace the holy water running from Tirta Empul Temple. Ticket masuk 20rb / orang , menggunakan kain sebagai penutup free of charge
review 2: The presidential palace Tapak Siring is one of the viral sites on the island of Bali. This place is very historic because many country leaders visit there. The place is very beautiful, clean, shady. The security is very tight so if you want to enter the palace you must follow the rules.
review 3: Best Presidential Palace ever in Indonesia. Don't return from Bali without visiting the Palace. Peace and tranquality with giant trees... Has a unforgettable view to Fountain Temple. Heaven in Bali....
review 4: Visited the palace on March 2022, but we didn't find out beforehand that it was closed for public during Covid.
review 5: This presidential palace is heritage from old empire at bali. Very unique with many kind of sparated houses for different purposes, trees and art. Pure water circulate in pool area, where king and queen had have cleaned themselves phisicly and mentally many years ago, and this ritual is still taken until now.

name: Warung Sripadi
address: Jl. Tirta Empul, Manukaya, Kec. Tampaksiring, Kabupaten Gianyar, Bali 80552, Indonesia
review 1: Very pleasant atmosphere. Friendly owner and clean , fresh food for the vegans ðŸ¥‘ The prices also very good. We came here twice and would come next time definitely ðŸ’¯ I am recommending this place for everybody, no matter , you are vegan or not ðŸ™ŒðŸ»
review 2: Great vegan restaurant super close to the Tirta Temple. The locations is nice, clean and cozy. The waiter was very kind and attentive. The food came quickly and it was tasty, the portions were good and also the price was good. Highly recommended:)
review 3: WOW!!! We pulled over randomly because we were hungry and had no idea we were going to get the absolute best food in Bali. This place is worth a trip all in itself. What kind people (even by Bali standards) and the food is SO UNBELIEVABLY GOOD. This is the best vegan food Iâ€™ve ever had.
review 4:
Great vegetarian cafe near Tirta Empul Temple. I was greeted very warmly! The food was delicious, I particularly liked pumpkin soup. The menu is rather limited, mostly based on local cuisine. Yet for me it was enough. Juice is cheap, but with added water, be ready )) Ball coffee is kind of viscous (thick), which is unusual, but I liked it.

The place has spacious parking, so no problem if you drive a car.
review 5: The vegan Nasi Campur and the "Meat"Ball Soup tasted great. The Pineapple and Watermelon Juice were good too. I recommend the Hot Turmeric Tamarind! The service was friendly and attentive.

However, some of the dish ingredients, like the seafood, appeared to have been pre-prepared. Additionally, the restrooms were dirty, and we had to negotiate our seating arrangements several times.

review 3: I really enjoyed my soup, chicken satay and sampler platter.  Western or traditional Balinese seating tables.

Vegetable salad - very fresh and crunchy

Very nice restaurant with nice bali food. Nice service. Big portion, free mineral water, free fruit after meal.
Very big portion.

name: Waroeng De Koi
address: Jl. Tirta Empul, Manukaya, Kec. Tampaksiring, Kabupaten Gianyar, Bali 80552, Indonesia
review 1: A place with "western food" like they say. Hard to understand what the dish is about, but like any place in Bali, it is a warm place with nice people. Not so much of a recommended restaurant...
review 2:
Love the environment. Super chill location close to the temple. Although the food was okay. The vibe of this restaurant was super pretty and filled with Bali vibes.

Simple come here for a drink or a simple mie goreng would never go wrong.
review 3: Food was nice with very quick service, really recommend the spring rolls
review 4: If your driver took you here, you managed to order already, itâ€™s too late to leave and you are worried of what might happen to your belly, worry no more. The food isnâ€™t great, but is not that bad either. Itâ€™s a decent restaurant with decent food. Enjoy your stay and donâ€™t bother too much bcs youâ€™ll be alright.
review 5:
Very nice place for amazing food after the temple.

Very nice views wherever you sit, you gotta order the duck its just delicious.

I appreciate their hospitality, they are so kind and always watch you to serve you the right way. Bless them

name: Sukabali Agro
address: H8M8+33R, Jl. Tirta, Manukaya, Kec. Tampaksiring, Kabupaten Gianyar, Bali 80552, Indonesia
review 1: First, I was not sure about visiting any Luwak coffee farms as they are not sustainable in many places. However, I had a feeling that the animals are treated well here, and this was confirmed by the staff. They explained a lot about the coffee-making process and different plants. After that, you get an amazing coffee and tea tasting. You can buy some of their products, but you are not forced to do so. We really enjoyed it there.
review 2:
Really lovely experience here. Our guide was very knowledgeable and there was no pressure at any point to purchase anything in the shop. An excellent selection of teas and coffees available for tasting and even a couple of little dogs running around saying hi to everyone.
The view is absolutely lovely it feels a very unique experience right down amongst the rice terraces. Couldnâ€™t recommend it enough.
review 3: Really lovely plantation! It was a great experience, free coffee tour! We bought some of their products Although they never pressured us to buy, they are truly warm and friendly people!  Also we realized that they offer swim service at excellent prices. Go and have a peaceful timeâ¤ï¸
review 4: It was a wonderful experience. The tasting was free and our guide was kind and didn't put pressure on us to buy something, he has great knowledge about the process of making coffee. Don't forget to support the local businesses. Weâ€™ll be back, no doubt that.
review 5: We were randomly taking photos in a rice field near. A very friendly man from Sukabali approached us to come visit. We had an amazing tasting of tea and coffee (for free!). It was SO GOOD! And afterwards we ordered one of our favourite coffees. It is really an oasis with all natural products. They also have a shop. Really worth visiting. I also saw they have the big bali swing, and not so many tourists. They also have some rescued dogsðŸ¥°

They were nice to change the plate but it took a while.
review 3: Wonderfull environment with a view over the rice fields, delicious food and friendly service...clear menu and cheap ....come and eat in a piece of paradise
review 4: Love the cafe and their bagel, total deliciousness. Also lovely decor.
review 5: Very nice view but bit pricy food which is ok-good quality and taste. Had some mie Goreng which was served with sate chicken and egg.

name: Warung Babi Guling
address: H8M8+F26, Jl. Tirta Empul, Manukaya, Kec. Tampaksiring, Kabupaten Gianyar, Bali 80552, Indonesia
review 1:
Food : 5 star. Soup is very rich with herby flavourings. Portion is regular.
0 star for the price. We were charged 60k for a portion of nasi babi guling with soup. Definitely a tourist trap for a basic food outlet setting.
review 2: Service was okay but a bit slow (considering there were 3-4 staff). The food was flavourful however the portion of the babi guling was very little for 70,000. The crispy chicken with fried noodles were okay. The fried noodles were very very spicy, even for us who love to eat spicy food. The price of the crispy chicken with fried noodles on the menu was 22,000 but when we paid they said it was 45,000 because the one posted was the old price. Definitely not worth the money eating here. There are better warungs around.
review 3: Its a trap for the tourist because they charge more than the original price. I recommend to find another babi guling that is worth the price not here at warung babi guling. They charge us 70k but if you go to other babi guling it is only 30-40k.

name: Abisha Mystique Villa
address: H8M7+7RV, Jl. Tirta Empul, Manukaya, Kec. Tampaksiring, Kabupaten Gianyar, Bali 80552, Indonesia
review 1:
This is my absolute happy place. So much so that we had our wedding there to share it with as many people as possible.
The villa is tucked away in its own jungle,  overlooking a valley of rice fields yet boasts complete privacy. It is only a short trip to central Ubud for shopping and sightseeing, but far enough that the only sounds you will hear are waterfalls and the occasional rooster or distant ceremony. The villa is periodically visited by a private chef if you wish and the staff are incredible. Nothing is too much trouble. Be sure to thank them.
For us, it wouldn't be a trip to Bali without a trip to Villa Abisha
